martin bojowald albert einstein institute potsdam and pennsylvania state university loop quantum cosmology abstract loop qu page 1 martin bojowald albert einstein institute potsdam and pennsylvania state university loop quantum cosmology abstract loop quantum cosmology is based on techniques which have been developed for a background independent quantization of gravity in cosmological situations they give rise to several basic effects which in turn have many physical applications the formalism will be reviewed in a self contained manner showing the emergence of quantum effects from the mathematical foundation as well as their naturality in a background independent theory these effects have immediate consequences for more complete universe scenarios including cyclic models most applications are based on effective equations which will be put in the general context of higher curvature formulation of gravity
